description: Latin destinatus. Computing use by analogy with originate.

adjectives.description: destinate (comparative more destinate, superlative most destinate)

verbs.description: destinate (third-person singular simple present destinates, present participle destinating, simple past and past participle destinated)

entries.meaning: (possibly nonstandard) To set a destination for (something), to send (something) to a particular destination.
examples: Now days, it can probably be done with a programming setup in the originating/destinating switches, and not involve a full time channel.

entries.meaning: (possibly nonstandard) To be scheduled to arrive at, as a destination.
examples: Prices for a mail piece weighing up to a half-pound range from $12.60 if it destinates in zones 1 and 2 to $19.50 if it destinates in zone 8.
